	(text_box "Idea: \n0.Initially everything after SW1 is low\n1.When pressing SW1 the LMC555 after a brief moment TR sets the output Q and disables the discharge DIS\n1.1 At the same time the capacitor on THR gets charged and PSU_EN enables the PSU\n2.Opening SW1 now disables the 555 as a semi floating pulldown, which lets PSU_EN stay high by itself\n2.0 Due to leakage to other parts the capacitor on THR will be charged further\n3.When pressing SW1 again the 555 THR threshold will be either reached already by 2.0 or after holding SW1 for long enough\n4.This will disable Q and enable DIS to discharge the capacitor at THR\n5.The output will stay low until SW1 is lifted again"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 88.9 86.36 0)
		(size 96.52 25.4)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "4db60fba-ad5d-4dcc-b6ec-b4af8965b0da")
	)
